To begin with git,you must first have the necessary information,like what git is about,its uses and its features. Below are few things
you should know:
Created by Linus Torvalds,
creator of Linux, in 2005
– Came out of Linux development community
– Designed to do version control on Linux kernel
GitHub was developed by Chris Wanstrath, P. J. Hyett, Tom Preston-Werner and Scott
Chacon using Ruby on Rails, and started in February 2008.

• Goals of Git:
– Speed
– Support for non-linear development
(thousands of parallel branches)
– Fully distributed
– Able to handle large projects efficiently
